g.text: Each individual network (ESXi, vMotion & Virtual SAN)needs a pool of IP addresses. This means each ESXi host will be given its own IP address for each network.
You can (well, you should) designate each networkits own subnet.

If you want to add one or more appliancestogether to create a cluster, make sure eachpool has an additional 4 IP’s per appliance.
